items.name: LISA: The Pointless SOTW Sprite Generator
items.description:
A new and improved sprite model trained on the battler sprites from LISA: The Pointless SOTW! This model is a LOT better than my previous LISA sprite model, which was trained on Painful sprites.

This is a lora trained on a whopping 176 sprites of characters from LISA: The Pointless SOTW! It was trained at a huge 896x896 resolution, which helps with the 'pixel art' style a lot. I training it mostly on the human fighters, so few animals and no joy mutants or shadow monsters. I'm VERY satisfied with the results of this LORA, I wasn't sure if it'd work out since I was trying a lot of new training techniques, but it came out great compared to the last one. It was trained on danbooru-style tags, so use those when trying to prompt - I've included the tags in a .txt file in the "Training Images" download below.

IMPORTANT: This was trained on the Fluffyrock 896 multi-resolution model. It won't work with pretty much any other model, so please make sure to use this model, or any of the newer higher res Fluffyrock models when generating anything.

NOTES:

-You must generate with the Fluffyrock model, and ideally, you should generate at 832x832 resolution (lora was trained at 896x896, but Fluffyrock only supports up to 832x832). Although I've had success at different resolutions, lower ones like 576x576 might get a little weird.

-I specifically tagged infinity franchise members as "jerseyhead", so use that if you want a character wearing that funny 88 jersey

-Changing the aspect ratio from a square will also work, although all trained images are square, so keep that in mind.

-You can actually have detailed background, if you put "purple background, simple background" in negative prompt, and describe the background you want in the main prompt. Keep in mind all trained images have a purple background.

-It can do concepts that weren't trained, such as women, or vehicles or what-not, so try it out in those regards. In fact, I guess this could be a 'LISA-styled' lora, since it can do landscapes and backgrounds.

-It wasn't trained on any joy mutants, however it can still do monsters and gross creatures pretty well if you prompt it good enough.

CREDITS:

Austin Jorgensen - Creator of LISA
Edvinas Kandrotas - Creator of Pointless

All the devs on SOTW - They made most of these sprites!

MrFood - He made this model, I'm just uploading it in his place :P

items.name: Cute Animals
items.description:
Cute animals are beloved creatures that bring joy and warmth to our lives. They often possess endearing features, playful behaviors, and irresistible charm. Here are a few examples of cute animals:

1. Kittens: Known for their fluffy fur, tiny paws, and curious nature, kittens are adored for their innocence and playful antics.

2. Puppies: With their floppy ears, wagging tails, and wide-eyed expressions, puppies exude cuteness and evoke feelings of love and companionship.

3. Bunnies: Soft and gentle, bunnies captivate with their fluffy coats, twitching noses, and adorable hoppy movements.

4. Pandas: These gentle giants steal hearts with their iconic black and white fur patterns, round faces, and playful nature.

5. Hedgehogs: With their prickly spines and tiny snouts, hedgehogs have a unique charm that has made them popular in the cute animal category.

6. Red pandas: Resembling a mix of raccoons and foxes, red pandas are known for their bushy tails, masked faces, and playful climbing skills.

7. Baby elephants: With their large floppy ears, innocent eyes, and playful nature, baby elephants are undeniably adorable and cherished by many.

8. Otters: These aquatic creatures are known for their playful behavior, holding hands while floating on their backs, and melting hearts with their cute antics.

9. Koalas: With their fluffy ears and round faces, koalas have a charming and cuddly appearance that has made them popular icons of cuteness.

10. Baby ducks: With their fluffy feathers, tiny wings, and adorable waddling, baby ducks are a delight to watch and are often associated with cuteness.

These are just a few examples of the many cute animals that capture our hearts and bring smiles to our faces. Their innocence, charm, and sometimes comical behavior remind us of the beauty and joy found in the animal kingdom.

items.description:
Easy image quality that has a good context awareness!

This model was mixed with the intent of having great image quality, and good context awareness. It will respond to most types prompting styles, wether it be descriptions, lyrics, or simply tags. Masterpiece is not required, none of the images posted have 'masterpiece, best quality', or anything along that line. The image quality is good by default!

V1.1 Update summary

Much better context awareness, small loss of hand quality.

The continuation of a weird model!

Having used alfahentai for lot random art, it was only being held back by it's own confusion at times. This model is built upon the idea to get rid of that confusion and make a confident model. All the images i posted are only using Nerfgun3's Negative Hand embedding. The rest is pure txt2img prompt. No inpainting or other manipulation was done.

Big shoutout to Cryonicus, I want to believe his model was the missing part my model needed. Make sure to give his model a try too!

What this model is and isn't

Unfortunately, getting the art to improve to an incredible standard, it cost the model it's ability to make proper genitalia. Breasts still work though. Again, the model has been merged as much so that it retains it's general knowledge. It does NOT respond well booru specific tags/prompts. It might have recollections of some things you might expect in a lot of booru tagged models. For example Wariza doesn't function. Masterpiece has essentially been removed as tag and is generally not needed at all. For all the images I create, unless I stole someone's prompt, it will not have masterpiece/best quality ever. Honestly, i've tried comparisons and generally doesn't seem to add anything.

This model shines in it's ability to grasp concepts, context and general cohesion. I've tried various prompting styles on this model and they all seem to work. It works best with natural language and descriptions.

Model Usage

The model works best on a low CFG, i stick at 5. At 6 you already start getting the first symptoms of burn, at 7 it's really bad, and 8 and above simply seem unusable. The model has a lot of detail it can resolve, so it likes high stepcount, like it's predecessor. With UniPC and cfg 3 or 4 you test prompts with steps as low as 7. Take note, that sometimes your prompt will be interpreted differently if you change the aspect ratio. The unpruned image has a bit better image quality in my experience.

Sampler: UniPC

CFG: 5

Steps: 20-50

Clip skip: 1

Upscale: 4x Ultrasharp, denoise 0.5

Negative prompt used

negative_hand, (low quality:1.3), (worst quality:1.3), (lowres:1.3), (error:1.3), (fault:1.3), (undefined:1.3), (crude:1.3), jagged, spiky, ugly hands, extra arm, extra hand, split arm, missing finger, extra finger, three fingers, four fingers, six fingers, (disfigured:1.3), (unclear:1.3), (indistinct:1.3), merged fingers, (bad anatomy,:1.3) misplaced hand, misplaced foot,, cleavage, sex, nsfw, ecchi, slutty, leotard, (text:1.3), (signature:1.3), (title:1.3)

modelVersions.name: v1.20
modelVersions.description:
Generate using a weight of 0.4-1 like this: <lora:Ultronv120:0.8>


How I archived my generations:

  1. txt2img: DPM++ SDE Karras with 20 steps,512x512(can go up to 768 for wide or tall), Restore faces on (using CodeFormer weight 1.0 in Settings), Hires-fix on, to 1024x1024 (double original size) with your preferred upscaler and Denoise 0.5, CFG 7. Then send to img2img!

  2. img2img: DPM++ SED Karras with 20 steps, Restore faces on (CodeFormer weight 1), rescale to 1536x1536, CFG 7, Denoise between 0.3-0.7 (based on how much you want to improve the image), SAME PROMPT! Send to extras when happy with img2img/inpaint results.

  3. extras: Scale to x3 (final will be 4608x4608, I suggest going lower, I did x3 just for the samples here) Upscaler 1 - FatalAnime 4x, Upscaler 2 - SwinIR 4x with 0.10 visibility, GFPGAN 0.10 visibility, CodeFormer 0.10 visibility.

items.name: 【Character】Kii (Azur Lane)
items.description:
Introduction

A LoRA model of Kii from Azur Lane. The trigger tag is 'kii \(azur lane\)'. The key features are 'fox ears, ponytail, open clothes, open kimono'. The 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) are recommended. 0.6 ~ 0.8 weights are good. The preview images are generated using 1.6 version (original) YesMix.

Cautions (Must Read)

For anime model,

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

pls disable 'face restoration' during generating.

  • Some preview images are generated using 'Hires Fix' and upscaled using 'SD Upscale'. Thus, if you wanna generate the preview images, pls download the original preview images and analyze them using 'PNG INFO' in webui to get all generating information.

BTW, make sure set this option in 'Stable Diffusion' settings to 'CPU' to successfully regenerate the preview images with the same seed.

  • The training resolution of this model is 1024x1024, so generating resolution must not exceed this range. Try to use 'hires fix' to prevent this problem and help to generate higher-resolution images.

  • For 784mb VAEs (NovelAI, Anythingv3, Orangemix, Counterfeit) users, make sure add '--no-half-vae' in command line of webui to prevent generating black images. See voldy's log for the details of edit method. For high-performance GPU, make sure 'medvram' and 'lowvram' mode are disabled.

items.name: Black_White
items.description:
Note: May not work well with other embeddings, although feel free to see if increasing the weight of the embedding using (brackets:) helps in that case.

This embedding will allow you to force an image to be colored, black and white, or both. It can be called with just "b_w".

When using it in your positive prompt, think of it as pouring a big bottle of black and white onto your painting.

When using it as your negative prompt, think of that exact scene but in reverse.

It does sometimes refuse to work, but I find it a pretty handy tool so I decided to share it. ^.^

items.name: Rosario Dawson
items.description:
A commission of @Zorglub.

Rosario Dawson is an American actress of Cuban and Puerto Rican descent, known for her roles in many films, such as Sin City or Men in Black, and TV shows such as The Mandalorian.

This TI has been a tough one to train... I've had to repeat the process from scratch a couple of times, mainly because I couldn't get the eyes right. Reduced the dataset to 12 images, then removed some more pics and added a few new ones... I'm satisfied with the final results, but I may still update the embedding at a later point.

This is step 1325 of a TI trained on a dataset of 15 images. I used my standard settings.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of (r0sd4wn-1325:0.99), a woman, RAW, close portrait photo, long brown coat, ((turtleneck sweater:1.2), trousers, long haircut, slim body, (high detailed skin:1.2), 8k uhd, dslr, soft lighting, high quality, film grain, Fujifilm XT3 sharp focus, f 5.6"
